-- Putin Energy Chief Sechin May Leave Government, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2012-03-19T04:25:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/putin-energy-chief-sechin-may-leave-government-vedomosti-says.html
IgorSechin, Russian Prime Minister
Vladimir Putin’s deputy in charge of the  energy industry , may
leave his post when Putin switches jobs with President Dmitry Medvedev, Vedomosti reported, citing four unidentified
government officials with knowledge of the matter.  Sechin may be replaced by  Sergei Kiriyenko , currently the
head of state nuclear holding Rosatom, the Moscow-based
newspaper reported today.  Sechin declined to comment, telling the newspaper it should
be renamed “Rumors” if it doesn’t verify its information,
Vedomosti said in a separate article.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
 skravchenko@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
